data.caption:
Hey ChatGPT, is everything OK?

Users started to wonder whether OpenAI's chatbot was malfunctioning after it spouted "Spanglish."

It's an embarrassing moment for a company that has raised billions of dollars.

To read more about what's going on with ChatGPT, click the link in our bio.

Story by Hasan Chowdhury.

(Credit: Markus Schreiber/AP, Tyler Le/BI)
#chatgpt #openai #ai #artificialintelligence

Nvidia chips remain in high demand, especially from tech companies.

Its CEO told analysts the company was trying its best to allocate them fairly.

Mark Zuckerberg recently said Meta would own more than 340,000 Nvidia H100 chips by the end of 2024.

Tap the link in our bio to find out more about Nvidia chips.

Story by Beatrice Nolan

(Credit: Getty Images/Reuters/BI)

#MarkZuckerberg #AI #tech

Google says it plans to fix issues flagged with its AI model, Gemini.

Users complained Gemini generated historically inaccurate images of people of color.

On Thursday, the company said in a statement sent to Business Insider that it was pausing Gemini from generating AI images of people while it makes the changes.

Head to the link in our bio to read more about the inaccuracies and Gemini's temporary pause.

Story by Joshua Zitser

(Credit: Getty Images)

#AI #google #gemini

Thousands of tech workers are on the job hunt after brutal layoffs and changed industry dynamics.

An experiment found it's easy for people to cheat in tech job interviews with ChatGPT.

It's also tough to get caught, which may lead to changes in how companies conduct tech interviews.

Head to the link in our bio to read more about how ChatGPT might be used to breeze through early rounds of interviews.

Story by Kali Hays

(Credit: Getty Images)

#AI #chatgpt #techjobs #interviews

A man created a female AI influencer in order to make money after losing his job.

"Kimochii" gained 43,000 Instagram followers with her racy content.

But the creator doesn't interact with fans directly and this made it harder to monetize.

Tap the link in our bio for more info about this AI influencer.

As told to Marta Biino

(Credit: Kimochii)

#AI #influencer #socialmedia

A Cybertruck engineer, Wes Morrill, commented on concerns the EV develops rust spots in the rain.

Morrill said the orange specks, merely the size of a pinhead, were probably surface contamination.

His comments came after some Cybertruck owners claimed the truck could rust in the rain.

Tap the link in our bio for more info about these claims.

Story by Grace Kay

(Credit: Getty)

#Tesla #ElonMusk #electricvehicles #transportation

Tiffany Fong uploaded a photo of what appears to be a scruffy-looking Sam Bankman-Fried to X.

The content creator said she got the photo from an inmate and ex-gang member called "G Lock."

"I've heard that he's not showering very much," Fong said of Bankman-Fried.

Tap the link in our bio to read the latest on Sam Bankman-Fried in prison. 

Story by Kwan Wei Kevin Tan 

(Credit: Getty Images)

#SamBankman #Tech #Crypto #FTX

Sam Altman just reminded everyone why OpenAI is leading the pack.

This time, it’s not because of a shock ousting from OpenAI, nor is it because of anything to do with ChatGPT. Instead, it’s because new text-to-video AI model called Sora.

Sora, unveiled on Thursday, can create videos up to a minute long from text, and its ability to produce high-fidelity videos has shocked the interenet.

For the full story, including more on how Sora works and a look at the kinds of hyperrealistic videos it can produce, head to the link in our bio.

Story by Hasan Chowdhury.

(Credit: Getty Images; Jenny Chang-Rodriguez/BI)

#tech #samaltman #openai #ai #sora

Mark Zuckerberg said that tech layoffs since the pandemic are due to multiple factors.

The first wave was due to a course correction from pandemic-era growth and overhiring.

Meta's CEO said more recent layoffs are because companies realized being leaner can make you "more efficient."

Click the link in our bio to read more about  Zuckerberg's comments.

Story by Ana Altchek.

(Credit: Getty)
#markzuckerberg #meta #techlayoffs #technews

Beond, an airline operating only business-class services, has announced plans to give an Apple Vision Pro to “select passengers” on some of its flights.

It bills itself as the world’s first premium-leisure airline, where every seat can lie flat.

But Beond’s shortest route is still double the length of the Vision Pro’s battery life.

To read more about the airline’s plan, click the link in our bio.

Story by Pete Syme

(Credit: Getty)

#apple #visionpro #airline #virtualreality #beond

Google is planning to use satellite data, AI technology, and computing power to map methane emissions.

Methane is a potent greenhouse gas that’s responsible for nearly a third of global warming.

Nearly 40% of manmade methane comes from oil, gas, and coal operations.

Click the link in our bio for more on the new map. 

Story by Catherine Boudreau. 

(Credit: Google) 
#google #tech #science #greenhousegas #climate

Jack Dorsey once led a Twitter company retreat to boost employee morale and set a vision for the company.

The 3-day event featured strange wellness routines, dance parties, and a special message from no-show guest Elon Musk. 

The following is an excerpt from "Battle for the Bird," a new book by journalist Kurt Wagner. 

Tap the link in our bio to read more about the Twitter company retreat and what it entailed. 

Story by Kurt Wagner

(Credit: Tyler Le/BI)

#Twitter #Tech #JackDorsey #Musk

Dan Ginn originally purchased a smartwatch to increase his step count and track his workouts.

As it began to track more data, he spiraled into a world of obsessive checking and health anxiety.

Since giving up his smartwatch, Ginn has dramatically improved his physical and mental health.

Click the link in our bio to see how he did it. 

Essay and photo by Dan Ginn. 
#applewatch #smartwatch #tech #health

Nvidia's CEO questioned Sam Altman's reported attempts to raise up to $7 trillion to boost GPU chip supply.

Jensen Huang told the World Governments Summit in Dubai that the cost would be far lower. 

He said building AI data centres globally would amount to just $2 trillion over the next five years.

Read more about the future of AI at the link in our profile.

Story by Jyoti Mann

(Credit: Noah Berger)

#ai #gpuchip #datacenter #openai #nvidia
E-waste thrown away every year is worth an estimated $60 billion. But extracting it requires expensive machinery worth thousands. #ewaste #waste #electronic

Tech workers have had to learn a hard lesson: layoffs can happen at companies that are doing just fine too.

Companies from Grammarly to Microsoft have laid people off in 2024 despite healthy finances.

Their decisions have been about getting resources focused on their most pressing goals.

Read more about the newest wave of layoffs at the link in our profile.

Story by Hasan Chowdhury

(Credit: Getty)

#tech #layoffs #microsoft #grammarly #finance

Jack Dorsey was at the Super Bowl.

He wore a t-shirt that says “Satoshi,” emblazoned in the style of a Nirvana t-shirt.

The mysterious Satoshi is said to be the inventor of Bitcoin.

Tap the link in our bio for more Super Bowl coverage.

Story by Lina Batarags 

#Tech #JackDorsey #Bitcoin #Superbowl

This week Jeff Bezos sold 12 million shares of Amazon stock, netting about $2 billion.

It's Bezos' first major sale of stock in the company since 2021.

The move puts him within reach of overtaking Elon Musk as the world's richest man.

Click the link in our bio to read more about Bezos' move.

Story by Katherine Tangalakis-Lippert.

(Credit: Getty Images)
#jeffbezos #amazon #elonmusk #tesla #billionares

The reviews are in, and the tech press is lauding the Apple Vision Pro headset for delivering on the company’s promises. 

Still, this is a new gadget frontier. The Vision Pro, like the similarly kitted-out Quest 3 and Quest Pro headsets from Meta, uses what’s known as “passthrough” video — cameras and other sensors that capture imagery of the outside world and reproduce it inside the device.

That, unfortunately, could have some very weird and very messy consequences for the human brain.

Click the link in our bio to read more about how the Vision Pro might be bad for you. 

Story by Adam Rogers. 

(Credit: Apple; Mike Kemp/In Pictures via Getty Images; Alyssa Powell/BI)
#tech #applevisionpro #visionpro #vr

OpenAI CEO Sam Altman has met with officials from the United Arab Emirates to pitch his plan to build lots and lots of new chip factories, according to The Wall Street Journal. The cost? $5 trillion to $7 trillion.

OpenAI needs more computing power (currently, it relies on Microsoft for this) — and this means it needs more silicon chip factories. A lot more. And chip plants ain't cheap.

But that kind of number isn't typically something a relatively new company thinks about raising. 

For the full story, including how much $7 trillion really is in perspective, head to the link in our bio.

Story by Katie Notopoulos.

(Credit: Jack Guez/AFP via Getty Images)

#openai #samaltman #tech #siliconchips #siliconvalley

Tesla announced pay increases for factory workers effective January 8.

It now pays US factory workers $22 to $39 an hour, according to documents seen by Business Insider.

Take a look at how much Tesla factory workers make across the country.

To see the full chart of pay data by region and tier, click the link in our profile.

Story by Grace Kay

(Credit: Getty)

#tesla #minimumwage #salary #texas #california #factoryworker
Facilities extract precious #metals from circuit boards using either brute force or an acid bath. #ewaste #recycling

Apple is working on prototypes of iPhones that could fold in half, according to a new report.

Apple has weighed foldable devices for years, and prototypes don't guarantee a future launch.

Samsung, Google, and others have released their own foldable phones in the midst of a resurgence.

Head to the link in our bio to read more about the possibility of foldable devices from Apple.

Story by Sarah Jackson

(Credit: Getty Images)

#apple #appleproducts #foldablephone

Katie Notopoulos’ beloved TikTok, the app she used to spend endless hours delighted by, has changed. 

The emphasis on shopping and TikTok Shop ads has really bummed Notopoulos out.

There’s something else off – there’s a sameness, and less of the surprising whimsy that made it fun.

Tap the link in our bio to read more about TikToks recent flop, and let us know your thoughts. 

Story by Katie Notopoulos

(Credit: NurPhoto)

#TikTok #Tech #Socialmedia #Business

Tesla is asking managers to identify the most vital roles on their team, Bloomberg reported.

The company also reportedly canceled some employee performance reviews.

During Tesla's latest earnings call, Elon Musk warned of a sales slowdown.

Click the link in our bio for everything we know.

Story by Grace Kay.

(Credit: Getty Images)
#tesla #layoffs #techlayoffs #elonmusk
